West Africa’s largest airline, Air Peace, has announced addition of Boeing 737-800 New Generation aircraft to its fleet as it prepares to expand internal operations. The company which announced the addition on Friday, said it will help boost its operations. The Boeing 737 Next Generation are narrow-body aircraft powered by two engines and produced by Boeing Commercial Airplanes.
Launched in 1993 as the third generation derivative of the Boeing 737, it has been produced since 1996 and is an upgrade of the 737 Classic (−300/-400/-500) series. It carries between 108 to 215 passengers.